{"questionId":"22463538","questionHtml":"<p>Find an expression for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math>, in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>, for this solution.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>∫</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>y</mi></mrow></msup><mi>d</mi><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>∫</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>x</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>y</mi></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; (A1)(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note: <em>A1</em></strong> for left hand side, <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for right hand side.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>substituting in&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>c</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; (A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> The substitution may be seen and credited later, however at that point the constant term may be <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>y</mi></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>M1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note: </strong>Award<em><strong> M1 </strong></em>for use of log law.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[7 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22463538","referenceCode":"24M.2.AHL.TZ1.5b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find an expression for y, in terms of x, for this solution.","paper":"2","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 7]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.14—Setting up a DE, solve by separating variables"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}